olive oil
1 bag broccoli florets
1 packet couscous
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
¾ cup boiling water
1 bag baby spinach leaves
2 packet beef strips
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 tsp honey
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
drizzle vinegar (balsamic or white wine)
¼ cup water

• Boil the kettle. Cut any larger broccoli florets in half.
• Place couscous and chicken-style stock powder in a large heatproof bowl.
• Add the boiling water (¾ cup for 2 people / 1½ cups for 4 people) and stir to combine.
• Immediately cover with a plate and leave for 5 minutes. Fluff up with a fork, then stir through baby spinach leaves and set aside.

• Meanwhile, heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook broccoli with the water and cook, tossing, until tender, 8-10 minutes.
• Transfer to bowl with couscous.

• Discard any liquid from beef strips packaging. In a large bowl, combine beef strips, garlic & herb seasoning and a drizzle of olive oil.
• Return frying pan to high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. When oil is hot, cook beef strips in batches, tossing, until browned and cooked through, 1-2 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, add the honey and toss to coat.
TIP: Cooking the meat in batches over a high heat helps it stay tender.

• Add a drizzle of vinegar to the couscous and toss to combine. Season to taste.
• Divide broccoli couscous between bowls and top with Mediterranean beef.
• Drizzle with dill & parsley mayonnaise to serve. Enjoy!